==Equipment==
{{Quote|Howard Stark fished that out of the ocean when he was looking for you. He thought what we think; the [[Tesseract]] could be the key to unlimited sustainable energy.|[[Nick Fury]] to [[Steve Rogers]]|The Avengers}}
*'''[[Tesseract]]''': Stark found the Tesseract where it had [[Battle in the Valkyrie|fallen]] into the ocean and began studying it while working for [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] while holding the Tesseract at [[Camp Lehigh]]. Unable to understand the Tesseract, Stark worked with [[Anton Vanko]] on the [[Arc Reactor]] and a [[Tony Stark's New Element|new element]] in hopes of understanding it further. Realizing that he would not be able to fully understand the Tesseract, Stark relinquished it to [[Project P.E.G.A.S.U.S.]]
{{Quote|Howard said the [[Arc Reactor]] was the [[Tony Stark's New Element|stepping stone]] to [[Tesseract|something greater]].|[[Nick Fury]] and [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 2}}
*'''[[Arc Reactor]]''': In his attempt to understand the [[Tesseract]], Stark worked with [[Anton Vanko]] to develop a large arc reactor, which could provide sustainable energy. He built one large enough to power [[Stark Industries Headquarters]], hoping that it would lead to the discovery of a [[Tony Stark's New Element|new element]] that would render nuclear power obsolete. However, [[Stark Industries]] stopped making breakthroughs in the technology.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Stark Mansion]]''': Stark owned a mansion in [[New York City]] which he used as his primary residence. Over time, Stark had made a family with his [[Maria Stark|wife]] and his [[Tony Stark|son]], all while creating technology in a vault within the basement of his mansion.
*'''[[Strategic Scientific Reserve Brooklyn Facility]]''': Once a secret facility hidden in an antique shop and run by the [[Strategic Scientific Reserve]] during [[World War II]], Stark and the other members of the SSR, oversaw the completion of the laboratory that became the house of [[Project Rebirth]] in the SSR's [[Brooklyn]] facility. Using [[Steve Rogers]] as a test subject, Stark operated the tech they used with [[Vita Radiation]], in order to help become a super soldier.
*'''[[Strategic Scientific Reserve Headquarters]]''': Stark visited the [[Strategic Scientific Reserve]]'s headquarters and tested new equipment. He gave [[Steve Rogers]] an improved [[Captain America's Shield|shield]] made of [[Vibranium]].
*'''[[Howard Stark's Penthouse|Penthouse]]''': Stark owned a penthouse in [[New York City]] that he let [[Edwin Jarvis]] and [[Peggy Carter]] use while working to clear his name of the [[Theft of Howard Stark's Technology|theft]] of his technology.
*'''[[Howard Stark's Warehouse|Warehouse]]''': Stark owned a warehouse which he used to store his prototype vehicles. Stark brought [[Dottie Underwood|Ida Emke]] to the warehouse. He was held hostage inside of the warehouse and hypnotized by [[Johann Fennhoff]] to pilot a plane and release [[Midnight Oil]] on [[Times Square]]. Stark was stopped by [[Peggy Carter]] and regained his senses.
*'''[[Howard Stark's Estate|Estate]]''': Stark got a defense contract moved to [[Los Angeles]] after he found he enjoyed the new scenery at his estate, bringing [[Edwin Jarvis]], [[Ana Jarvis]], and his pet flamingo [[Bernard Stark]]. [[Peggy Carter]] went to Los Angeles, and Stark allowed her to stay at the estate while investigating [[Isodyne Energy]]. He threw a pool party at the estate, which was interrupted so he could help Carter investigate [[Zero Matter]] in and planned to [[Infiltration into the Arena Club|infiltrate]] the [[Arena Club]]. Once Stark and Carter returned home, he worked with [[Jason Wilkes]] until he needed help from [[Abner Brody]] in [[Peru]]. Stark later returned to the estate and helped plan to defeat [[Whitney Frost]].
*'''[[Stark Pictures Studios Lot]]''': Stark founded [[Stark Pictures]] in [[Los Angeles]]. One of the first projects that Stark filmed on the studio lot was a comic book adaptation of ''[[Kid Colt, Outlaw]]''. Stark later used the studio as a place for the [[Strategic Scientific Reserve]] to capture [[Whitney Frost]].
*'''[[Camp Lehigh]]''': Once Camp Lehigh was transformed into one of the first S.H.I.E.L.D. facilities, Stark worked inside for research while it was supervised to protect the [[Tesseract]] and test [[Pym Particles]].
*'''[[Triskelion]]''': Stark did work for [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] at the Triskelion with [[Mitchell Carson]]. S.H.I.E.L.D. tried to replicate the [[Pym Particles]] from the [[Ant-Man Suit]], so [[Hank Pym]] confronted Stark, along with Carson and and [[Peggy Carter]], leading to an altercation between Pym and Carson. Stark attempted to stop Pym from quitting S.H.I.E.L.D., but Pym resigned and left the meeting.

